{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"0wm1lzmclqft0lamxe6cfcz","title":"OOP","desc":"","updated":1670696224807,"created":1670695470789,"custom":{},"fname":"programing.rust.OOP","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"5be5d140a2ecea3cdedb0e44c11fae9b","links":[],"anchors":{"object-oriented-programming":{"type":"header","text":"Object-Oriented Programming","value":"object-oriented-programming","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"objects-contain-data--behavior":{"type":"header","text":"Objects contain data & behavior","value":"objects-contain-data--behavior","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"encapsulation---hides-implementation-details":{"type":"header","text":"Encapsulation - Hides implementation details","value":"encapsulation---hides-implementation-details","line":16,"column":0,"depth":2},"inheritance---type-system--code-sharing":{"type":"header","text":"Inheritance - type system & code sharing","value":"inheritance---type-system--code-sharing","line":20,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["mu5z62gzma1l2d3ddoro770","oc8gik1ujqpi3kzjx7fbo6p"],"parent":"d81qplbgwaiawwudxe38xpf","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"oop\">OOP<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#oop\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"object-oriented-programming\">Object-Oriented Programming<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#object-oriented-programming\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch17-00-oop.html\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch17-00-oop.html</a>\n<a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch17-01-what-is-oo.html\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch17-01-what-is-oo.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"objects-contain-data--behavior\">Objects contain data &#x26; behavior<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#objects-contain-data--behavior\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Structs &#x26; enums have data, and <code>iplm</code> blocks provide methods on them.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"encapsulation---hides-implementation-details\">Encapsulation - Hides implementation details<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#encapsulation---hides-implementation-details\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Use <code>pub</code> keyword to decide which modules, type, functions &#x26; methods in our code should be public.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"inheritance---type-system--code-sharing\">Inheritance - type system &#x26; code sharing<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#inheritance---type-system--code-sharing\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Inheritance: an object can inherit elements from another object's definition.</li>\n<li>Reuse code: using default trait method implementations</li>\n<li>Polymorphism: substitute multiple objects for each other at runtime if they share certain characteristics.\n<ul>\n<li>Rust use <strong>generics</strong> to abstract over different possible types &#x26; trait bounds to impose contraints on what those types must provide (bounded parametric polymorphism)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/mu5z62gzma1l2d3ddoro770\">State-Pattern</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/oc8gik1ujqpi3kzjx7fbo6p\">Trait-Objects</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"xfkxbponh0sohobo6pual15","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1668137379975,"created":1663481872547,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"cb44915142ec96bef8f764f3dc90389e","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-my-page":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to my page","value":"welcome-to-my-page","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"contacts":{"type":"header","text":"Contacts","value":"contacts","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"dendron":{"type":"header","text":"Dendron","value":"dendron","line":18,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["u5a2e2vvfn3x7k0shuvmb1b","qw8y69zxn8wr7tzz4gtcrrv","q7qw45jglqwmynary64q67c","6wjqcjgkrpeqtmzb1o8o1q